    155 if ('address.' === attr.slice(0, 8)) {
    156 value = (ref4 = addresses[i]) != null ? ref4[attr.slice(8)] : void 0;
    157 } else if ('card.' === attr.slice(0, 5)) {
    158 value = (ref5 = cards[i]) != null ? ref5[attr.slice(5)] : void 0;
    159 } else {
    160 value = dancer[attr];
    161 }
    162 cell = {
    163 value: value,
    164 autoWidth: true,
    165 hAlign: 'left',
    166 borders: { top: borderH }
    167 };
    168 if (cell.value != null) {
    169 switch (attr) {
    170 case 'birth':
    171 cell.value = cell.value.format('DD/MM/YYYY');
    172 break;
    173 case 'address.phone':
    174 case 'cellphone':
    175 cell.value = cell.value.match(/.{1,2}/g).join(' ');
    176 break;
    177 case 'card.knownBy':
    178 cell.value = function () {
    179
    var k, len1, ref6, results1;
    180 ref6 = cell.value;
    181 results1 = [];
    182 for (k = 0, len1 = ref6.length; k < len1; k++) {
    183 key = ref6[k];
    184 results1.push(i18n.knownByMeanings[key] || key);
    185 }
    186 return results1;
    187 }().join(',');
    188 }
    189 }
    190 if (first) {
    191 first = false;
    192 } else {
    193 cell.borders.left = borderV;
    194 }
    195 results.push(cell);
    196 }
    197 return results;
    198 }());
    199 }
    200 return writeFile(filePath, xlsx(content).base64, 'base64', function (err) {
    201
    return done(err);
    202 });
    203 });

    };
    205 }(this));

    602 1 Import.prototype._convertValue = function (attr, value, index) {
    603
    var format, j, k, lValue, len, len1, ref2, ref3, val, values;
    604 if (index == null) {
    605 index = 0;
    606 }
    607 if (_.isNumber(value)) {
    608 if (isNaN(value)) {
    609 return void 0;
    610 }
    611 value = '' + value;
    612 }
    613 if (!_.isString(value)) {
    614 return void 0;
    615 }
    616 if ((attr === 'firstname' || attr === 'lastname' || attr === 'email' || attr === 'phone' || attr === 'cellphone' || attr === 'birth') && 0 <= value.indexOf(',')) {
    617 values = value.split(',');
    618 return this._convertValue(attr, values[index >= values.length ? values.length - 1 : index]);
    619 }
    620 lValue = value.toLowerCase().trim();
    621 switch (attr) {
    622 case 'firstname':
    623 case 'lastname':
    624 case 'street':
    625 case 'city':

    627 case 'title':
    628 if (0 <= lValue.indexOf(',')) {
    629 return function () {
    630
    var j, len, ref2, results;
    631 ref2 = lValue.split(',');
    632 results = [];
    633 for (j = 0, len = ref2.length; j < len; j++) {
    634 val = ref2[j];
    635 results.push(this._convertValue('title', val));
    636 }
    637 return results;
    638 }.call(this);
    639 } else {
    640 if (lValue === 'melle' || lValue === 'mlle' || lValue === 'melle.' || lValue === 'mlle.') {
    641 return 'Mlle';
    642 } else if (lValue === 'mme' || lValue === 'madame' || lValue === 'mme.' || lValue === 'me') {
    643 return 'Mme';
    644 } else {
    645 return 'M.';
    646 }
    647 }
    648 break;
    649 case 'email':
    650 return lValue;
    651 case 'phone':
    652 case 'cellphone':
    653 case 'zipcode':
    654 value = lValue.replace('+33', '0').replace(/\D/g, '').trim();
    655 if (value === '') {
    656 return null;
    657 } else {
    658 return value;
    659 }
    660 case 'knownBy':
    661 return _.compact(_.uniq(function () {
    662
    var j, len, ref2, results;
    663 ref2 = lValue.split(',');

    253 invoice.changeDate(date);
    254 return Invoice.getNextRef(date.year(), date.month() + 1, teacher, function (err, ref) {
    255
    if (err != null) {
    256 return done(new Error('failed to get next ref for new invoice ' + err.message));
    257
    }
    258 invoice.ref = ref;
    259 return invoice.setCustomers(dancers, function () {
    260
    return invoice.save(function (err) {
    261
    if (err != null) {
    262 return done(new Error('failed to save new invoice ' + invoice.toJSON() + ': ' + err.message));
    263
    }
    264 return done(null, invoice);
    265
    });
    266 });
    267 });
    268
    };
    269 }(this));
    270 },
    271 roundEuro: function (num) {
    272
    var cents, floor;
    273 floor = Math.floor(num);
    274 cents = Math.floor(100 * num) % 100;
    275 if (cents === 0) {
    276 return floor;
    277 } else if (cents <= 50) {
    278 return floor + 0.5;
    279 } else {
    280 return floor + 1;
    281 }
    282 }
    283 };
